definition:
πνευματικός, -ή, -όν
 (πνεῦμα), 
  1. of or caused by the wind, air or breath (Arist., al.). 
   2. spiritual (opposite to σωματικός, Plut.); 
   (a) of created beings : τὰ π. (RV, the spiritual hosts), Eph.6:12; of that which is related to the human spirit, opposite to ψυχικός, 1Co.15:44 15:46; 
   (b) of that which belongs to or is actuated by the Divine Spirit; 
   α of persons : 1Co.2:15 3:1 14:37, Gal.6:1; οἶκος π., figuratively, 1Pe.2:5; 
   β of things : Rom.1:11 7:14, 1Co.2:13 10:3-4 12:1 14:1, Eph.1:3 5:19, Col.1:9 3:16, 1Pe.2:5; opposite to τ. σαρκικά, Rom.15:27, 1Co.9:11.†
 SYN.: ψυχικός, which see, and cf. DB, ii, 410, iv, 612  (AS)
